import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    for source in data['source'].unique():
        source_data = data[data['source'] == source]
        plt.plot(source_data['year'], source_data['net_generation'], label=source)

    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Source', loc='best')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum')
    pivot_data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of net generation by source?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Net Generation")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title="Source", loc="upper left")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_net_generation = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].mean()
    ax = avg_net_generation.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple'])
    plt.title('What is the average net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Source')
    plt.ylabel('Average Net Generation')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Net Generation'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_pivot = data.pivot_table(index='source', columns='year', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.heatmap(data_pivot, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='.2f')
    plt.title('What is the total net generation by year and source?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Source')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(rotation=0)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.plot(kind='scatter', x='year', y='net_generation', alpha=0.5)
    plt.title("What is the correlation between net generation and year?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Net Generation")
    plt.legend(["Net Generation"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
